ssed through the redemptive dynamic of doubt, can contribute to developing a postsecular apologetic for faith.This book can function both as an accessible introduction to Westphal for those who have not read him extensively and also as an informed critical appreciation and extension of his work for those who are more experienced readers.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 03. Jan 2023) 0aHermeneuticsxReligious aspectsxChristianity. 0aKnowledge, Theory of (Religion). 0aPhilosophical theology. 4aPhilosophy & Theory. 4aReligion. 4aTheology. 7aPHILOSOPHY / Epistemology.2bisacsh1 aBenson, Bruce Ellis, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCaputo, John D., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDesmond, William, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aEvans, C. Stephen, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFerreira, M. Jamie, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHart, Kevin, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKearney, Richard, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMatuštík, Martin Beck, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aOlthuis, James H., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPutt, B. Keith, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPutt, B. Keith, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aWestphal, Merold, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWyscogrod, Edith, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertFordham University Press Complete eBook-Package Pre-2014z978311118960408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe